"Domain-generation algorithms (DGAs) allow attackers to manage infection-spreading websites and command-and-control (CaC) deployments by altering domain names on a timely basis. DGAs have made the infection and CaC architecture more robust and supportive for attackers. This detailed taxonomy of DGAs highlights the problem and offers solutions to combat DGAs through detection of drive-by download and CaC activity from the compromised machine."
